 Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Hugh Hubeck was born in 1270, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Miss CORBET."},"et":{"1270–":"1270–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1316–Male":"1316–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","1270":"1270","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1270–":"1270–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1316–Male":"1316–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","1270":"1270","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1270–":"1270–Décédé","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1316–Male":"1316–Décédé","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","1270":"1270","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir Hugh Hubeck est né en 1270, à Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Miss CORBET."},"de":{"1270–":"1270–Verstorben","1300–Female":"1300–Verstorben","1316–Male":"1316–Verstorben","1270–Male":"1270–Verstorben","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","1270":"1270","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Sir Hugh Hubeck wurde 1270 in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. 